Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and carr woodland; conifer plantations; ancient pine woodland; wetlands including water meadows, sedge bed, wooded river banks and lake shores, bogs; grassland (including calcareous); gardens; old hedges; saltmarsh; dunes; coastal clay cliffs. Reared from fallen beech trunk and rotten wood. ii–xi.
